mics are affected by contracts, salaries, the structure of careers, and institutional conditions. The analyses cover the full spectrum of the academic profession, including part-time jobs and short-term contracts, both in public and private institutions. The book also addresses what universities must do in order to attract young, qualified candidates.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCollege teachersxEmploymentvCross-cultural studies. 0aCollege teachingvCross-cultural studies. 0aUniversities and collegesxFacultyvCross-cultural studies. 4aBusiness and Economics : International Management. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Educational Administration. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aAltbach, Philip G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAltbach, Philip G., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBalbachevsky, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinkelstein, Martin J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasanefendic, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorta, Hugo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIglesias, Kevin W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJayaram, N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehm, Barbara M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKyvik, Svein, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Yi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLiu, Nian Cai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMusselin, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo